g.text: Ticketmaster is an online platform that allows users to purchase ticket for concerts, sports events, theater, and other live entertainment
- Customers to discover upcoming events, browse seat maps, purchase tickets securely, transfer or resell them, and access digital tickets for entry.
+ They should also be able to resell or transfer tickets when permitted.
- Event organizers and venues to create events, configure seating charts, define pricing tiers, and monitor sales in real time. (TODO)
- Gate agents to validate tickets quickly at scale, even under poor connectivity, while preventing duplicate or fraudulent entries. (TODO)
- Users should be able to book a ticket
- Users should be able to view an event
- USer should be able to search an event
- System should be able to scale to support popular events with high active users
- System should be highly available with low-latency for viewing events
- System should be highly consistent for booking tickets
- Captures changes in Postgres such as inserts,
updates, and deletes and replicates to Elasticsearch
